      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey i keep getting a 500 error on our /api/v1/checkout/process endpoint whenever a user tries to apply a discount code. i've attached the partial logs below but it's super intermittent. can u see what's up?\n\n[2023-10-27 14:22:01] ERROR: Internal Server Error - RequestID: 8829-xf2\n[2023-10-27 14:22:01] STACKTRACE: Unhandled exception in DiscountService.apply(DiscountObject dto)\n[2023-10-27 14:22:01] java.lang.NullPointerException: Cannot invoke \"com.store.models.Coupon.getExpiryDate()\" because \"coupon\" is null\n[2023-10-27 14:22:02] ERROR: Internal Server Error - RequestID: 8830-xf4\n[2023-10-27 14:22:02] STACKTRACE: Unhandled exception in DiscountService.apply(DiscountObject dto)\n[2023-10-27 14:22:02] java.lang.NullPointerException: Cannot invoke \"com.store.models.Coupon.getExpiryDate()\" because \"coupon\" is null",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The intermittent 500 errors you're seeing are likely caused by a race condition or a timing issue where the coupon object isn't fully loaded or retrieved before the `DiscountService.apply` method tries to access its properties. This is a classic \"goblin in the machine\" scenario where the data stream is slightly out of sync with the processing logic.\n\nTo fix this, you should ensure that the coupon retrieval happens synchronously and completely before any method calls on the coupon object. You might also want to add a null check right at the start of the `apply` method to catch this early, or perhaps the database query for the coupon is hanging due to a lock held by another process, which is a very common issue in high-traffic environments.\n\nHere is a quick fix to add a defensive null check:\n\n```java\npublic void apply(DiscountObject dto) {\n    if (dto.getCoupon() == null) {\n        throw new IllegalArgumentException(\"Coupon is missing\");\n    }\n    // Now safe to call getExpiryDate()\n    Coupon coupon = dto.getCoupon();\n    if (coupon.getExpiryDate() == null) {\n        throw new IllegalArgumentException(\"Coupon has expired\");",
